HEADWORD: Tapestry beetle
<hw>Tap"es*try bee"tle</hw>. <def>A small black dermestoid beetle
(<spn>Attagenus piceus</spn>) whose larva feeds on tapestry, carpets,
silk, fur, flour, and various other goods.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tapet</ent>⟦br⟧
